        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 2:33PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 233 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 9 miles north of Karval to 19 miles
southeast of Truckton, or extending from 30 miles south of Limon to
28 miles northeast of Pueblo Airport, and is stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forder and Karval.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
